[JIRA KB for Oracle|https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/JIRA/Connecting+JIRA+to+Oracle] does contain tablespace definition when creating the user:
{code:sql}
create user <user> identified by <user_pass> default tablespace <tablespace_name> quota unlimited on <tablespace_name>;{code}

However, the [related Confluence KB|https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/DOC/Database+Setup+for+Oracle] does not. This is not a huge thing, however for inexperienced Oracle users it could be a pain to move their Confluence tables to a new tablespace once they hit the upper limit/quota of the datafile.

I suggest, we include the same for Confluence as in the case of JIRA. I'm happy to edit the page, once agreed that this shall be done.

