In preparation for upgrade to Confluence 5.1 from 4.1.9, we've found that the 'Select All' and 'Deselect All' functions in the 'Actions' drop down on the Edit Permissions page no longer works for individual users. The problem appears to have to do with space-permissions-min.js trying to do a string replace on the username variable. Since our usernames are all numeric, the functions mentioned above fail. Works fine for groups and 'anonymous' since the values there are always strings. Adding a toString() to the code that does the replace should fix this.

